            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="734" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d734">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Korea/2–1348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Political Adviser in Korea</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jacobs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-13">February 13,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83. Cite <gloss target="#t_Zpol1">Zpol</gloss> 180. Learned this morning <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Commission after rather heated debate with
                    Jackson and Djabi on one side and Liu and Paul-Boncour on other rejected
                    proposals of Jackson and Djabi to submit to Interim Committee Subcommittee I
                    report on unsatisfactory conditions in South Korea.</p>
                <p>Commission then decided merely to request Interim Committee whether, in view of
                    Soviet boycott, elections should be held in South Korea to choose consultative
                    representatives under resolution 1 or to choose representative assembly under
                    resolution 2.</p>
                <p>Commission is now meeting to approve summary of proceedings of Subcommittee 2
                    (task of which is to examine documents received and secure statements from
                    Korean personalities) and Subcommittee 3 (dealing with elections and election
                    laws). These Menon will take with him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jacobs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
